22/02/2008
ANKARA, Turkey -- The General Staff confirmed on Friday (February 22nd) that it has launched a ground operation into northern Iraq to destroy camps used by the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK).
The military added that the troops would return as soon as the "planned goals were achieved".
They repeated the attack is aimed only at the PKK and denied rumours of clashes with Iraqi Kurdish militia members.
(Hurriyet, Zaman, NTV - 22/02/08;
AFP, Reuters - 21/02/08)
